[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(13) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Thou bearest record of thyself; thy record is not true.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Better, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou bearest witness of Thyself; Thy witness is not true.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Comp. Note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 5:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) The Authorised version here, by a change of word, renders the connection less obvious than it really is. The Pharisees, standing probably in the front of the crowd listening to Him, bring a technical objection to His statement, and one which He had Himself admitted the force of. “According to your own words,” they mean, “what you now say is not valid.” They stand in the light of day, but demand a formal proof that the Sun has risen.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John 8:13-14",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 8:13-14",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Pharisees, therefore ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Namely, some of them who were then present, but different persons from those who had brought in the woman, being enraged at the late disappointment of their brethren; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "said unto him, Thou bearest record of thyself ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— And therefore, by thine own confession, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thy record ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Or testimony, rather, as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μαρτυρια ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "signifies; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "is not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to be admitted as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "true ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— But may rather be suspected of vain glory. They retort upon our Lord his own words, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 5:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "If I testify of myself, my testimony is not true. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He then added, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "There is another who testifieth of me. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To the same effect he replies here, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Though I testify of myself, yet my testimony is true ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— For I am inseparably united to the Father. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I know ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— And from firm and certain knowledge proceeds the most unexceptionable testimony; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whence I came, and whither I go ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— To these two heads may be referred all the doctrine concerning Christ. The former is treated of, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.; the latter, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For I know whence I came ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I came from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "God, both as God and as man. And I ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "know ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "it, though ye do not.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
