  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Pharisees therefore said unto him,.... On account of his declaring himself the light of the world: these were either the same who went out of the temple, filled with remorse of conscience, and were now returned, and bearing him a grudge, came to take some advantage against him, if they could; or they were others of the same complexion, sent by them, to make their observations on him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "thou bearest record of thyself. The Ethiopic version renders it, \"dost thou thyself?\" which does not seem so decent and comely; see  Proverbs 27:2; though it does not follow, that what a man says of himself is not truth, as these suggest: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "thou bearest record of thyself. The Ethiopic version renders it, \"dost thou thyself?\" which does not seem so decent and comely; see  ",
