            "class": "",
            "text": "; though it does not follow, that what a man says of himself is not truth, as these suggest: ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "thy record is not true; for John testified of himself, that he was not the Christ, nor Elias, nor that prophet; but the voice of one crying in the wilderness; and this testimony he bore of himself, at the importunity of the Jews themselves, John 1:19; and his testimony was true; so was that which Christ bore of himself; but their sense rather seems to be, that it was not firm and authentic, and would not pass in any court of judicature, since no man can be a witness in his own cause. ",
